{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, future research should compare multiple LLMs (GPT-4, Mistral, Claude, Bard, Perplexity, Claude, Bard, Perplexity, etc.)",
    "to find which ones are most appropriate for each clinical application.A critical challenge is that LLMs are prone to \"hallucination\" -the generation of false content due to an LLM's extrapolation of its training data [18].",
    "There are several examples in the literature [19,20].",
    "Hallucinations and inaccuracies with LLMs will be a barrier to clinical adoption for medico-legal reasons, as the uncertain legal status of these models puts providers at risk.",
    "This must be addressed by the medical community before such technologies can be deployed."
  ]
}